title: Full Body Stretch | Mobility Routine for Flexibility & Relaxation
description:
Ready for a Smooth Stretch Routine? I love doing Mobility Workouts before Bed, or after my workout, but you can do it whenever you want - as long as you're doing it!

Mobility is Key for many Exercises, so make sure to work on your full range of motion next to strength and hiit training!

WORKOUT DETAILS

👉🏼 No equipment
👉🏼 50-60 seconds on each exercise
👉🏼 No Repeat

 
D I S C L A I M E R

Tabata is an advanced level of the workout and is not suitable for beginners. If you are a newbie start with simple and easy exercise before attempting Tabata. Performing Tabata, in the beginning, might strain your muscles and you may get injured.

comments: Love this, no time wasted with excessive talking!  Great! Love the preview of the next exercise....makes this so smooth! Great job!
I've done this twice now and I have to say it's grounding at the end of a workout and I feel wonderful when I'm finished. So calming.

I love that you show the next move and that there is an alarm letting know when to pass to the next move. In that way, we don’t have to break our neck to look at the screen while doing a pose, it’s flown and very pleasant. Did this one after a cardio workout and it was super relaxing.
This 52 yr old needed that.  I’m just getting back to working out and not doing a good job of stretching.  So thank you for doing this, it was a great start to my day!
